        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 12:03PM PDT by NWS Eureka CA</headline>
        <description>At 1202 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers near
Klamath, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hazardous conditions to motorists Exercise caution when
driving over small hail.

Locations impacted include...
Klamath Glen and Klamath.
</description>
        <instruction>Small hail can quickly accumulate on roadways resulting in slippery
conditions. Go easy on brakes and steering to avoid spin-outs.</instruction>
